Everything compiles clean and all tests pass. Here's the full picture of what we built:

---

## What changed

### New files

**`src/lib/create-primary-scale.ts`** — generates a 12-stop primary scale from per-range from/to luma, shared chroma+hue, with override hooks:

```
darks:   d10 ← lerp(from=0.202, i=0)  →  lerp(to=0.438, i=3) = d40
mids:    m10 ← lerp(from=0.483)       →  lerp(to=0.742)      = m40
lights:  l10 ← lerp(from=0.825)       →  lerp(to=0.94)       = l40
```

**`src/lib/create-palette.ts`** — builds a 16-color palette from 6 light anchors (auto-derives dark* variants, plus black/gray/lightGray/white from primaries)

**`src/lib/create-primary-scale.test.ts`** — 8 tests (generation, overrides, reversed range, completeness)

**`src/lib/create-palette.test.ts`** — 6 tests (default derivation, custom factor, overrides, primaries mapping, completeness)

### Updated files

**`src/themes/terra/black-atom-terra-fall-day-next.ts`** — uses both new builders. From 30 lines of getter boilerplate to 25 lines of declarative config:

